e tax burden each party bears. In this linear case, the exact sharing depends on the slopes of the demand and supply curves. The deadweight loss calculation indicates the efficiency loss due to the tax, which is $\$2.75$ billion per year, but it does not directly determine the sharing of the tax burden."
